-- U.S. mortgage applications fell last week -MBA
-- 
-- Wed Mar 19, 2014 07:00AM EDT
-- None



NEW YORK, March 19 (Reuters) - Applications for U.S. home mortgages fell last week as both purchase and refinancing applications slipped, an industry group said on Wednesday.

The Mortgage Bankers Association said its seasonally adjusted index of mortgage application activity, which includes both refinancing and home purchase demand, fell 1.2 percent in the week ended March 14. The MBA's seasonally adjusted index of refinancing applications fell 1.3 percent, while the gauge of loan requests for home purchases, a leading indicator of home sales, dipped 0.9 percent.  <^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^ GRAPHIC U.S. mortgage data: http://link.reuters.com/guv37s  ^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^> Fixed 30-year mortgage rates averaged 4.50 percent in the week, down 2 basis points from 4.52 percent the week before.